The emir of Fika and chairman of the Yobe State Council of Chiefs, Dr Muhammad Ibn Abali Muhammadu Idrissa, has distributed food items to 500 orphans, internally displaced persons (IDPs), widows, physically challenged and aged ones to sustain them during the Ramadan. Over 300 persons benefited the package in 15 districts of the emirate, 27 IDPs from Kiriwa area of Borno State who live in Potiskum town, Ngalda IDPs, the physically-challenged in Kampa among others. The monarch said that the food items, which were donated to the emirate by the Yobe State government through State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA), included 100 bags of 50kg rice, 20 jerry cans of 25-litre vegetable oil, 20 cartons of tomato paste and 10 cartons of Tin Geisha (fish). Our correspondent who was at the venue of the event, reports that each of the 500 beneficiaries got a package containing 10kg of rice, one tin of tomato paste, one litre of vegetable oil and one tin of Geisha (Fish). On behalf of the beneficiaries, the head of the cripples’ association, Hassan Baba Dada, thanked the monarch for the gesture. Alhaji Idrissa was assisted in the distribution of the food items by the director of personnel management (DPM) in Potiskum local government area, Ibrahim Yayangida Abubakar.